T1  - Preferential trading agreements and capital flows
AU  - Webb, Michael A.
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
SP  - 181
EP  - 190
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/01/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(90)90057-I
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030438789090057I
AB  - A three-country trade model is used to determine the impact of a preferential trading agreement between two countries on world prices and the international allocation of capital. Assuming the agreeing countries have characteristics typically associated with developing countries, we derive a simple condition that predicts whether a country experiences an inflow or outflow of capital with the agreement. While at least one country experiences a capital inflow, the other may experience an outflow. Welfare implications are addressed.
