T1  - Measuring inequality change in an economy with income growth: Reassessment
AU  - Moore, Robert E.
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 32
IS  - 1
SP  - 205
EP  - 210
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/01/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(90)90059-K
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030438789090059K
AB  - This paper reassesses an article by Fields which criticizes using standard income inequality indices for the evaluation of high income sector enlargement growth. This paper dissents in three ways: the intuition that motivated Fields' paper is found to only partially account for the changes occurring during growth; the inequality index that Fields developed is shown to incorporate the concept of ‘symmetry’; and the concept of inequality as the expected experience of income differences is shown to support the use of the standard indices.
